            <div class="clearfix text-formatted field field--name-field-body field--type-text-long field--label-hidden field__item"><p>The Nepean Visual Arts Centre offers specialty arts classes taught by accomplished artists - painters, potters, illustrators, sculptors, photographers - in custom studio spaces for participants of all levels of ability. Students experience a diversity of arts instruction in a creative and dynamic environment.</p>
<p>Participants also have the opportunity to display their artwork at Nepean Visual Arts Centre’s studio gallery.</p>
<p><span><span><span><span>Exciting opportunities are available to young artists as well - find out more about&nbsp;</span></span></span></span><span><span><span><a href="https://ottawa.ca/en/arts-heritage-and-events/funding-calls-and-opportunities/young-art"><span><span><span>Young at Art</span></span></span></a></span></span></span><span><span><span><span>.</span></span></span></span></p>
<p>Our sister facility, The <a href="https://ottawa.ca/en/recreation-and-parks/recreation-facilities/facility-listing/nepean-creative-arts-centre">Nepean Creative Arts Centre</a>, has arts-specific studios available for rent, including music, dance, theatre and visual arts studios, a black box theatre, recital hall, set construction workshop, and meeting rooms for you to pursue your talents and artistic aspirations.</p>
<h3>Instructors</h3>
<p>Arts Centre courses are taught by talented artists. These teachers are specialists in their particular discipline or medium, with fine arts degrees, and/or exhibition experience to their credit. Our instructors guide students to see the world in a different way, learn about art, and help participants to express their feelings and ideas in a unique and powerful medium – the arts. They provide opportunities to explore, experiment, and have fun!</p>
</div>
      
